---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Article from "../../components/Article.astro";
---

<Layout title="dance of death">
  <Article
    title="dance of death"
    section="death"
    updated="archive draft"
  >
    <p>
      the dance of death is a symbolic image of mortality as an unavoidable
      companion. all people—regardless of status, role, or identity—are drawn
      into the same ending.
    </p>

    <p>
      kings, workers, priests, and fools all appear in the same procession.
      death does not differentiate between them.
    </p>

    <p>
      this image is not only about inevitability, but about exposure. what once
      seemed important loses its hierarchy.
    </p>

    <h2>equality</h2>

    <p>
      the dance removes distinction. social roles dissolve, leaving something
      more fundamental behind.
    </p>

    <p>
      this is not meant to erase life, but to reveal its structure.
    </p>

    <h2>irony</h2>

    <p>
      there is often a strange tone within the image—almost playful. death is
      not only feared, but shown as something that undercuts seriousness.
    </p>

    <p>
      in this way, the dance can feel both heavy and strangely light.
    </p>

    <h2>reminder</h2>

    <p>
      the dance of death functions as a form of memento mori. it reminds that
      life is temporary and should not be mistaken for something permanent.
    </p>

    <div class="mini-links">
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death">back to death index</a>
      <a class="link-blue" href="/death/grief">continue to: grief</a>
      <a class="link-red" href="/death/rebirth">rebirth</a>
    </div>
  </Article>
</Layout>